(155, 2, '2017-09-24 10:59:52', '2017-09-24 10:59:52', '<h3>INSERTING A LINK TO REDIRECT TO THE PROJECT INFORMATION\'S PAGE</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<hr>\r\n<code><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/projinfo?view=somerandomvalueofview\">Click me to see kung nagana na dynamic website creation ^.^</a></code>\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><em>http://localhost/wordpress/projinfo?view=somerandomvalueofview</em></strong>\r\nThat is the link that you will redirect with if everything is alright. If it works (:D), then.....<span style=\"line-height: inherit\">this is how you would create a link/reference from a project to its own information details page.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Include this line:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>&lt;a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/projinfo?view=insertprojnamehere\"&gt;Well you know how a tag works :)&lt;/a&gt;</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>insertprojnamehere</strong> - replaced with the project\'s name (spaces should be replaced with %20 check other things like this na lang, anyways automatic nagchachange ito if you use PHP\'s string variable)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDatabase still not configured so the default layout page will always be shown.\r\n\r\n<em>Once it\'s working, well then that\'s perfect. If not, don\'t worry. Everything\'s gonna be okay in the end. :)</em>\r\n\r\n   ! ! TEAM GAME!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n-\r\n\r\nLast updated: 09-24-17 8:32 PM', 'Project Info Linking', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'project-info-linking', '', '', '2017-09-24 12:32:42', '2017-09-24 12:32:42', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=155', 0, 'page', '', 0),
